    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of climbing shrub native to Eurasia; twines to 6 m (20 feet) in height. Its trumpet-shaped flowers arranged in whorled clusters are yellowish, purple-tinged blooms that are followed by red berries. Some of the garden varieties are prized for their fragrance.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
